---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`Events · ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Upcoming events from the Optimist Club of Mount Horeb, Wisconsin." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>

<!-- Page header -->
<section class="bg-white pt-16 pb-8">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-optimist-blue">What's coming up</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Event 1: Oratorical / SWIS conference — photo left, text right -->
<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-12 md:items-center">
      <div>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/events/2026-zonal.jpg" alt="Brittany and Ella at the Verona oratorical contest" class="w-full h-auto rounded-sm" />
          <figcaption class="mt-3 text-sm text-optimist-slate italic text-center">Brittany and Ella</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 md:mt-0">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-optimist-slate">Saturday, May 16</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-optimist-blue">Regional oratorical at Milwaukee</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-optimist-blue">
          <p>Last month in Verona, our Brittany Walton stood at the microphone for the zone-level oratorical contest. Her <a href="/someone-you-should-know/2026/january" class="underline hover:text-optimist-gold transition-colors">January Someone You Should Know</a> lays out a senior year already full to the edges &mdash; the Humane Society, her own gardening business, the food pantry, the Clothes Closet, hurricane relief supply drives, an Optimist event nearly every month. She made room for the oratorical on top of all of it. The time paid off. She finished third.</p>
          <p>Five kids competed at zonal. Two advance &mdash; Ella and Nimer take the stage at the regional oratorical contest on Saturday, May 16, at the Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee Northwest, presentations 9:00 to noon.</p>
          <p>Cheering for Ella and Nimer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Event 2: Frolic raffle — photo right, text left -->
<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-12 md:items-center">
      <div class="md:order-2">
        <img src="/images/events/frolic-raffle.webp" alt="Drawing a winning ticket at the Summer Frolic raffle" class="w-full h-auto rounded-sm" />
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 md:mt-0 md:order-1">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-optimist-slate">Drawing Sunday, June 14</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-optimist-blue">Summer Frolic raffle</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-optimist-blue">
          <p>Twenty dollars buys a ticket. The grand prize is ten thousand. There are fifteen cash prizes in all, and the drawing happens at 5:30 in the afternoon on Sunday, June 14, in the beer tent at Grundahl Park. You don't need to be there to win.</p>
  <p>Here's the part we want you to hear. The Frolic and the Optimists are teammates. The Frolic has been very generous to us over the years, and the proceeds from this raffle come right back to the local nonprofits and youth sports clubs that work the festival every June &mdash; us included.</p>
  <p>Tickets are at Miller &amp; Sons Supermarket and the Mount Horeb Area Chamber of Commerce, or from any of us &mdash; flag down an Optimist and we'll happily sell you one.</p>
  <p>It's a good ticket to buy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>